  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideTitle": "How Project Workbench works",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideIntro": "Project mode is not another chat page. It is the native OOB workbench for vibe projects, linking generated frontends, Project Tools, Workspace files, skills, and persistent data into one editable unit.",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideFlowTitle": "Interaction flow",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideFlowPrompt": "Prompt + Skill split the requirement",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideFlowProject": "Project registry records the container",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideFlowApi": "Project Tools register business capabilities",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideFlowDisplay": "Flutter Display renders the business frontend",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideFlowPersist": "data/ + logs/ persist AI and UI calls",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideProjectTitle": "What a Project binds",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideProjectBody": "A Project binds the goal, skill, Workspace files, Display list, Project Tools, data, and logs. It is not an MCP tool list and it is not a loose generated HTML page.",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideFrontendTitle": "How the frontend is shown",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideFrontendBody": "The generated frontend is an OOB-native Flutter Display. After Workspace switches to Project mode, it no longer shows a large manager list; it hosts the active Project home like an embedded browser window. One Project can own multiple Displays, selected from the small menu.",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideBackendTitle": "How the backend is called",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideBackendBody": "Backend capabilities are registered as Project Tools, such as todo.add and todo.finish. The AI layer and frontend buttons call the same workbenchApiCall(projectId, toolId, inputs) path. Project create, export, and delete remain control APIs and do not mix into business tools.",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideDataTitle": "How data flows",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideDataBody": "A call goes through Flutter -> MethodChannel -> OOB native executor, then writes to the Project data/ and logs/. Frontend refreshes, AI execution stats, and state after restart all come from this persisted data.",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideVibeTitle": "How to keep editing",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideVibeBody": "To continue vibe coding, go back to the main Home input and describe the change. The Workbench Skill decides whether to create a new Project, extend Project Tools, adjust Displays, or hot update the current Project.",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideExtendTitle": "Extending backend tools",
  "workbenchWorkspaceGuideExtendBody": "When adding a capability, define toolId, input/output schemas, executorKind, persistence files, and the frontend trigger first. Then register the Project Tool through Workbench interfaces; do not hand-edit registry files.",
